function sumByProperty(arr, prop) {
  let sum = 0;
  for (let I = 0; I < arr.length; i++) {
    let propValue = arr[i];
    let nestedProps = prop.split(".");
    for (let j = 0; j < nestedProps.length; j++) {
      if (propValue.hasOwnProperty(nestedProps[j])) {
        propValue = propValue[nestedProps[j]];
      } else {
        propValue = null;
        break;
      }
    }
    if (typeof propValue === 'number') {
      sum += propValue;
    }
  }
  return sum;
}
```
In this modified version of the function, we check if the `prop` parameter has any dots (indicating nested properties). If so, we split the `prop` parameter into an array of nested properties. We then iterate over this array and check if each property exists in the `arr[i]` object. If it does, we set `propValue` to be the value of that property. If it does not, we set `propValue` to `null` to indicate that the nested property chain is broken.

Once we have the `propValue` for the current object in the array, we check if it is a number and add it to the `sum` if it is. Finally, we return the `sum`.

